Example 1.

x <- seq(-3, 3, by = 0.01)
y <- x^3 - 5*x + 6
plot(x, y, xlim = c(-3, 3), ylim = c(-5, 15), type = "l")
abline(h = 0, v = 0, lty = 2)

plot(x, y, xlim = c(0.8, 1.2), ylim = c(1.6, 2.4), type = "l")
abline(h = c(1.8, 2.2), lty = 2)
points(x = 1, y = 2, pch = 20)
text(x = 1.04, y = 2.0, labels = "(1, 2)")

(xdelta <- seq(0.8, 1.2, by = 0.01))

2.4-12

x <- seq(-3.5, -2.5, by = 0.01)
y <- 1/(x + 3)^4
plot(x, y, ylim = c(0, 20000), type = "l")
abline(h = c(0, 10000), v = -3, lty = 2)

(xdelta2 <- seq(-3.2, -2.8, by = 0.01))
##  [1] -3.20 -3.19 -3.18 -3.17 -3.16 -3.15 -3.14 -3.13 -3.12 -3.11 -3.10
## [12] -3.09 -3.08 -3.07 -3.06 -3.05 -3.04 -3.03 -3.02 -3.01 -3.00 -2.99
## [23] -2.98 -2.97 -2.96 -2.95 -2.94 -2.93 -2.92 -2.91 -2.90 -2.89 -2.88
## [34] -2.87 -2.86 -2.85 -2.84 -2.83 -2.82 -2.81 -2.80
1/(xdelta2 + 3)^4 > 10000
##  [1] FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE
## [12]  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE
## [23]  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE FALSE FALSE
## [34] FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE
which(1/(xdelta2 + 3)^4 > 10000)

##  [1] -3.09 -3.08 -3.07 -3.06 -3.05 -3.04 -3.03 -3.02 -3.01 -3.00 -2.99
## [12] -2.98 -2.97 -2.96 -2.95 -2.94 -2.93 -2.92 -2.91 -2.90
plot(x, y, xlim = c(-3.2, -2.8), ylim = c(5000, 15000), type = "l")
